
3B SYNTAX

. Project Setup
Open terminal in your project directory and run:

npm install
This installs all dependencies listed in package.json.

3. Run the Server
In the same terminal:


node server.js
Or if you've added a start script in package.json:


npm start
Youâ€™ll see:


MongoDB Connected
Server running at http://localhost:3002
4. Install & Setup MongoDB Compass
ðŸ§­ Steps to Download & Connect
Download from: https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/compass

Install and open it.

For localhost (default MongoDB):

Connection string:


mongodb://localhost:27017
Click "Connect".

You should see your database wad4 (after first insert).

5. Test APIs Using Postman
ðŸ“¦ Steps to Download
Download from: https://www.postman.com/downloads/

Install and open it.

ðŸ§ª Testing CRUD APIs
POST (Create Item)

URL: http://localhost:3002/api/items

Method: POST

Body â†’ raw â†’ JSON:


{
  "name": "Sample Item",
